&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Staff Nurse to work within the Oncology OPD &amp; Chemotherapy Day Case Unit, within Plymouth Hospitals Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Outpatient clinics are held for both new &amp; follow up patients within the department. The Chemotherapy Day Case Unit delivers outpatient chemotherapy &amp; other treatments to patients with malignant conditions. The post is varied and interesting. They should also be interested in caring for patients with malignant conditions and providing holistic care to our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ideally the candidate should be Chemotherapy trained; Cannulation and venepuncture skills would be of benefit, however full training could be provided to the right candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Jenny White Senior Sister, or Tracy Taylor, Jacquie Lucas or Marie Soria Junior Sister’s on 430290 or Sharon Raymond Matron for Oncology &amp; Blood Services on 08451558155, Bleep 89138.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to internal Trust staff, as well as ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon who are able to display recent relevant experience as dictated by the Person Specification.***&lt;/p&gt;
